	<Title>
		High blood pressure: Can you prevent it?
	</Title>
	<Body>
		&lt;p&gt;High blood pressure can wreak havoc on your body for years without a single symptom. That&apos;s why early detection is so important. If you&apos;re diagnosed with high blood pressure or you simply want to keep high blood pressure at bay, healthy habits can make all the difference: 1. Eat healthy foods. Eat less saturated fat and total fat, and limit the amount of sodium in your diet. 2. Maintain a healthy weight. 3. Increase your physical activity. 4. Limit alcohol. 5. Don&apos;t smoke. 6. Manage stress.&lt;/p&gt;
